<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Avaunt" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Avaunt,</orth> exclamation of contempt or of abhorrence, uttered to drive one away: <cit><quote>childish fear, a.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 274" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 274</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>rogues, hence, a.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 90</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a., thou witch!</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 80</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.298" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 298</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.77" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.283" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 283</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 4, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.335" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 335</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.271" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 271</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.12.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 12, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 126</bibl>.<lb />Substantively: <emph>to give her the a.</emph> == to send her packing, <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 10</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>